snippet.textDisplay: I really don't think Wilder will be able to adapt and judging from what I heard from Jay Dea's that he wouldn't have thrown in the towel.. I don't think he understand his role as the head coach or that he can take Wilder to the next level. Also from what we have seen both Wilder & Jay both are just going along with this as it comes no plan what so ever.. plan A right hand, plan B right hand and plan z the right hand AGAIN.. nothing else.. and when the going gets tough Jay hides and sits his ass down and lets others take the tough decision like throwing the towel in.. Wilder needs to rest, recover and get back in the GYM with someone who knows what they are doing and teach Wilder the fundamentals..  boxing101 crash course.. maybe have couple of fights to practise on those new skills and get back in the ring with Tyson if he is still around or talk to WBC to make him mandatory for the WBC title again regardless who is holding it he can get his WBC belt back if he does the right thing.. However judging from his rookie and amerture performance against Tyson if he gets right back in.. it will be over.. GAME OVER.. Tyson will just dismantle him EVEN quicker and faster.. We may even get a KO at round 2 this time round .. Tyson can see the right hand before Wilder even thought of throwing the right hand.. so if he think he can catch Fury after 19 rounds of boxing and not fully clean catching him he is on pipe dream.. LOL
